---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Mortgage vs Rent: How to Calculate What You Can Afford" description="Compare renting vs buying with practical calculations. Learn mortgage affordability rules, hidden costs of homeownership, and when renting makes more sense." keywords="mortgage vs rent, mortgage calculator, rent or buy, affordability calculator, mortgage payment, housing costs, home buying guide">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Finance</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Mortgage vs Rent: How to Calculate What You Can Afford</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 10, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>The rent-vs-buy decision is one of the biggest financial choices you will make. While "stop paying someone else's mortgage" sounds convincing, the maths is more complex than it first appears. Here is how to compare the two fairly.</p>

      <h2>The 28/36 Rule for Mortgage Affordability</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">Housing costs should not exceed 28% of gross income</p>
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400 mt-1">Total debt payments should not exceed 36% of gross income</p>
      </div>

      <h2>True Cost of a Mortgage</h2>
      <p>A mortgage payment is just the beginning. True homeownership costs include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Principal and interest:</strong> Your monthly mortgage payment</li>
        <li><strong>Property tax:</strong> 1-2% of home value annually</li>
        <li><strong>Home insurance:</strong> $1,000-3,000+ per year</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Budget 1-2% of home value per year</li>
        <li><strong>HOA fees:</strong> $200-500/month if applicable</li>
        <li><strong>Closing costs:</strong> 2-5% of purchase price upfront</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>True Cost of Renting</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Monthly rent:</strong> Fixed (until renewal), predictable</li>
        <li><strong>Renters insurance:</strong> $15-30/month</li>
        <li><strong>Annual increases:</strong> Typically 3-5% per year</li>
        <li><strong>No maintenance costs:</strong> Landlord covers repairs</li>
        <li><strong>No property tax:</strong> Indirectly included in rent</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>When Buying Makes Sense</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You plan to stay at least 5-7 years (to recover closing costs)</li>
        <li>You have a stable income and emergency fund</li>
        <li>Local rent is high relative to mortgage payments</li>
        <li>You want to build equity and have a long-term asset</li>
        <li>Interest rates are favourable</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>When Renting Makes Sense</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You might relocate within 3-5 years</li>
        <li>Local property prices are extremely high relative to rents</li>
        <li>You value flexibility and mobility</li>
        <li>You can invest the difference between rent and ownership costs</li>
        <li>You do not want the responsibility of maintenance</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Quick Mortgage Payment Estimate</h2>
      <p>For a rough monthly payment estimate on a 30-year mortgage:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>$200,000 at 7%: approximately $1,330/month (principal + interest only)</li>
        <li>$300,000 at 7%: approximately $1,996/month</li>
        <li>$400,000 at 7%: approximately $2,661/month</li>
        <li>$500,000 at 7%: approximately $3,327/month</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Add 30-50% for taxes, insurance, and maintenance to get true monthly cost.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/loan" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Loan Calculator →</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
